cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SD

Reasoning: 

1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - This paper focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the communication between humans and robots, which is a key aspect of robotics research. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper covers both verbal and non-verbal aspects of human-robot communication, which involves natural language processing and understanding, falling under the domain of computation and language. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of robots as intelligent agents that can interact with humans, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper covers non-verbal aspects of human-robot communication, which includes sound-based communication, falling under the domain of sound.
